cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with image representation learning using adversarial networks and focuses on factors of variation such as identity, pose, illumination, and style. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method to evaluate conditional generative networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of adversarial training and variational autoencoders also suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the mention of face morphing suggests the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
